    <stitle>VT 365 Diesel Engine - 2004 Model Year - CRANKCASE, CRANKSHAFT and BEARINGS, CAMSHAFT and BUSHINGS - Removal
        - Piston Cooling Tubes
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s26508.1.5" svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Piston Cooling Tubes</title>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, the piston cooling tubes use a special patch type mounting bolt. Do not
                    substitute.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f2650812" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd06/D0617.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Piston cooling tube</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Piston cooling tube mounting bolt (patch type) (M6 x 18)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Piston cooling tube</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <para>Remove each piston cooling tube by removing its special patch type mounting bolt (M6 x 18). The bolts are
            reusable, providing you clean and inspect the bolt, and add Liquid Gasket (RTV) to bolt threads before
            reinstallation.
        </para>
    </svcproc>
